This paper deals with unsupervised discovery of speech features and linguistic units using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and speech recognition. The paper also involves the use of deep neural networks, which falls under the categories of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of unsupervised learning techniques, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also involves the application of spoken term detection, which falls under the category of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
